  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Asynchrony during mechanical ventilation has been poorly described in patients suffering from
      acute respiratory distress syndrome. The purpose of this study is to describe the frequency
      of asynchronies (ineffective efforts and double triggering) in these group and evaluate
      potential risk factors and prognosis implications.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
